You will be involved in the planning and management of civil engineering projects including infrastructural or geotechnical engineering works. &nbsp;You will need to conduct feasibility / environmental studies, analyse and provide solutions for civil engineering problems and prepare cost estimates &amp; schedules for civil engineering works. You will need to have good analytical and communication skills to manage infrastructure planning consultations with Agencies. &nbsp;You will also be responsible for coordination &amp; supervision of the tendering process, design works and projects management by private consultants. &nbsp;You will manage the projects to meet the budgets and timeline.



Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.